
MediaWiki
Use the MediaWiki dialogue box to add or edit your MediaWiki account settings.

Enter the URL of a MediaWiki server, starting with http://

Enter your user name on the MediaWiki server. Leave empty for anonymous access.

Enter your password on the MediaWiki server. Leave empty for anonymous access.

Enable to store your password between sessions. The master password must be enabled, see Tools - Options - %PRODUCTNAME - Security.
Enter the Internet address of a Wiki server in a format like http://wiki.documentfoundation.org or copy the URL from a web browser.
If the Wiki allows anonymous access, you can leave the account text boxes empty. Otherwise enter your user name and password.
If you have enabled the master password feature on the Security tab page of the Tools - Options - %PRODUCTNAME dialogue box, then the software can store your password and automatically insert the data where necessary. Enable the "Save password" checkbox to store your password.

